{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Although current large language models are effective in general domains, they often fail to meet the needs of catalytic scientists.",
    "Much of this inadequacy is attributed to the lack of reliable knowledge about catalysts, as relevant catalyst structural features and performance analyses are rarely present in commonly used pre-trained text corpora, such as C4 [13] and the Pile [14].",
    "Furthermore, the best performing large language models like ChatGPT are only served through APIs, which creates a barrier to research and progress in external domains.",
    "Fine-tuning open-source large language models is an effective way to meet domain-specific needs.Currently, fine-tuning open-source large language models have reached considerable success in fields such as biology, healthcare, and finance.",
    "In biology, a domain-specific pre-trained Transformer language model, BiOGPT [15], has been developed for biomedical text generation and mining."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Much of this inadequacy is attributed to the lack of reliable knowledge about catalysts, as relevant catalyst structural features and performance analyses are rarely present in commonly used pre-trained text corpora, such as C4 [13] and the Pile [14].",
